import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['open'] = pd.to_numeric(data['open'], errors='coerce')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['open'], label='Open')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'], label='Close')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between opening and closing prices?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['ret'] = pd.to_numeric(data['ret'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['ret'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['ret'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['ret'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['ret'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of returns on investment?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Return on Investment')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.boxplot([data[data['signal'] == 'short']['ret'], data[data['signal'] == 'long']['ret'], data[data['signal'] == 'neutral']['ret']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['short', 'long', 'neutral'], rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the relationship between trading signal and returns?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Trading Signal')
    plt.ylabel('Returns')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='ignore')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter(ticker.FuncFormatter(lambda x, pos: '' if x < 0 or x >= len(data['date']) else data['date'][x].strftime('%Y-%m-%d')))
    ax.xaxis.set_tick_params(rotation=90)
    ax.set_title('What is the volatility of the financial instrument?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.grid(True)
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['open'], 'g', label='Open')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['close'], 'r', label='Close')
    ax.fill_between(data['date'], data['low'], data['high'], facecolor='gray', alpha=0.5, label='Volatility')
    ax.legend(loc='upper left')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
